### Changes in this version (8.0.0-pre.4) since 8.0.0-pre.2

#### New features:
 - [%as:]: set local methods to hidden
 - [%as:]: added error reporting when trying to submit a method that does not exist
 - [%as:]: adjusted API for jobs to better include relationships
 - [%as:]: added support for submitting matrices with IDs & overrides
 - [%as:]: added initial support for supplying overrides for library methods
 - [%as:]: switched header in emails to inverted design
 - [%as:]: added domain to email CID
 - [%as:]: added HTML email template
 - [%as:]: added initial implementation of server mail
 - [%as:]: jwt signing can now use either RSA or ECDSA keys
 - [%as:]: increased duration on machine files to reduce check-out frequency
 - [%as:]: added network:timeout config option and implemented timeout for requests
 - [%as:]: added support for RI-J as well as RI-JK
 - [%as:]: added initial support for PySCF density fitting (SCF only for now)
 - [%as:]: added billing
 - [%as:]: servers now check cert age before refreshing
 - [%as:]: added more authentication levels to server endpoints
 - [%as:]: switched JWT key auth to using server certs
 - [%as:]: servers now check cert age before refreshing
 - [%as:]: digichemd executable now includes server by default
 - [%as:]: added digichemd startup script
 - [%as:]: updated service script
 - [%as:]: added service file for running with systemd
 - [%as:]: server objects now write their PID to a plaintext PID file
 - [%as:]: removed debugging
 - [%as:]: added temp debugging to slurm calls
 - [%as:]: added get_billing endpoint
 - [%as:]: added supports_billing property to destinations
 - [%as:]: SLURM account data is now returned in a proper hierarchy
 - [%as:]: added more descriptive error message for missing db
 - [%as:]: added initial endpoint for fetching billing
 - [%as:]: added get_billing_account() and get_billing() methods to SLURM
 - [%as:]: added BILLING status
 - [%as:]: added get_share_data() method
 - [%as:]: added support for using the submitting user's ID as the billing account
 - [%as:]: added support for sshare command
 - [%as:]: added better error message for when no local user credentials are available
 - [%as:]: added db_name property to database for better error reporting
 - [%as:]: added initial billing support to SLURM
 - [%as:]: added get_local_user() function
 - [%as:]: added user set and user info programs
 - [%as:]: added ability to specify login duration
 - [%as:]: added local user login functions
 - [%as:]: added abiltiy for server to listen on all hosts, added port to server config, and allowed 0 for keep_alive
 - [%as:]: greatly expanded firestore support
 - [%as:]: added better debug info when submitting info to DB after job completion
 - [%as:]: added better error reporting when parsing a malformed method
 - [%as:]: improved error messages in server locking
 - [%as:]: directory endpoint now uses user run dir
 - [%as:]: added option to disable combined reports
 - [%as:]: multi-user servers now use separate run dirs for each user
 - [%as:]: added safe_access to some server endpoints
 - [%as:]: switched firestore to use bulk_writer()
 - [%as:]: added better interfaces for fetching results from mongita and firestore DBs
 - [%as:]: removed unsupported unqlite
 - [%as:]: added initial user permission protection to job DB
 - [%as:]: added initial support for userIds in job and result database
 - [%as:]: added users/self endpoint
 - [%as:]: added /users/self end point to test user mechanism
 - [%as:]: Server now issues a warning if there is no authentication enabled at all
 - [%as:]: added authentication to all endpoints
 - [%as:]: added better error logging for user auth and added config option to enable or disable user auth
 - [%as:]: added initial ability to authorise users
 - [%as:]: finished adding support for firebase for main functions
 - [%as:]: started adding support for status keywords
 - [%as:]: added Status_keywords type
 - [%as:]: The digichem version is now printed to the main log file

#### Bugfixes:
 - [%as:]: added fix for servers on NFS using the same lock file across different nodes, that could leak to strange connection problems
 - [%as:]: fixed matrix submit expecting an input field in each method
 - [%as:]: fixed assigning to the object rather than dict in override
 - [%as:]: fixed trying to merge calc options into destination instead
 - [%as:]: fixed using dict as object in new jobs api
 - [%as:]: fixed firestore not writing sub collections if no id is provided for the main doc
 - [%as:]: fixed firestore crash if certain sub-collections aren't available
 - [%as:]: fixed Local (parallel) calling silico resume (fixes #203)
 - [%as:]: fixed missing sub-image labels in reports
 - [%as:]: fixed 'uer' instead of 'user' typo
 - [%as:]: fixed calculations not storing results under their associated user in the DB
 - [%as:]: fixed typo in email template
 - [%as:]: fixed not calling send_mail() method
 - [%as:]: added missing doc depends
 - [%as:]: added workaround for PySCF #3136
 - [%as:]: fixed duplicate dispersion property in PySCF
 - [%as:]: fixed using incompatible JWT algorithm
 - [%as:]: fixed digichem.service trying to start before network is up
 - [%as:]: fixed job crashed when no SLURM reason is available
 - [%as:]: fixed BILLING status being ignored
 - [%as:]: fixed using userID instead of user in call to get_billing_account()
 - [%as:]: fixed validation errors on queue usage
 - [%as:]: fixed SLURM billing
 - [%as:]: fixed missing billing endpoints
 - [%as:]: fixed get_billing() not fetching parents properly
 - [%as:]: fixed using list to catch exceptions
 - [%as:]: fixed some job endpoints not functioning
